text.tspan: The executable file is a "hybrid" (i.e. a fat binary) between an ELF
file and a JAR (derived from the Zip format). Much like SFX archives,
the file contains object codes at its head and has archived files and
central directory entries appended at its end.
Side note: main(), although it exists,
does not actually get invoked here.
(a.k.a. the duplicate-name directed-graph class linking problem)
Some methods and fields have the ACC_SYNTHETIC attribute,
which hides them from most IDEs, debuggers and some decompilers.
